---
import PublicationLayout from '../layouts/PublicationLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TAGLINE } from '../consts';
---

<PublicationLayout
  title='About'
  description='About the publication, editorial stance, and AI-assisted production approach.'
>
  <section class='about-hero'>
    <p class='kicker'>About the publication</p>
    <h1>Practical reporting on LLM products, AI agents, and the service economy around them.</h1>
    <p class='lead'>{SITE_TAGLINE}</p>
  </section>

  <section class='about-grid'>
    <article class='card panel'>
      <h2>What this publication covers</h2>
      <p>
        Signal & Circuit tracks the people and systems turning large language models into useful work.
        That includes builder tooling, agent workflows, release shifts, managed AI services, and the ugly
        operational realities that appear after the demo ends.
      </p>
      <p>
        The audience is two groups at once: developers shipping real products with LLMs, and operators or
        entrepreneurs using AI systems to solve narrow business problems in the field.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class='card panel'>
      <h2>Editorial stance</h2>
      <p>
        This is a practitioner-first publication. No empty hype, no press-release rewriting, and no fake
        certainty where the evidence is thin. If a workflow is messy, expensive, brittle, or only works in
        a sandbox, that matters.
      </p>
      <p>
        We care about what survives contact with real operations: support load, maintenance burden,
        deployment friction, pricing shifts, and whether a system still helps after the novelty wears off.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class='card panel'>
      <h2>How this prototype is produced</h2>
      <p>
        This site is part of a local Mission Control publication workflow. Planning, drafting, review, and
        site assembly can involve AI assistance, but nothing is treated as publishable just because a model
        produced it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Content is expected to move through a review pipeline before it is considered ready. This prototype
        exists to prove that the editorial system and the site experience can work together cleanly.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class='card panel disclosure'>
      <h2>Disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Articles on this publication may be produced with AI assistance and then reviewed for accuracy,
        structure, and usefulness before publication.
      </p>
      <p>
        This current site is a local-only prototype. Nothing here is public or live until Angel explicitly
        approves the later deployment phases.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</PublicationLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    max-width: 72ch;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    color: rgb(var(--muted));
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .panel {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .panel p {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .disclosure {
    background: rgba(var(--surface-strong), 0.7);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
